           <h2>Traveling by Car</h2>

<p><strong>From the North </strong></p>

<p>Take Hwy 401 to Hwy 427 South Exit at Dundas St. (Also known as Hwy 5). Make a left on Dundas St. and then make another left at the first set of traffic lights, Cloverdale Mall Rd. This will lead you directly into the shopping centre parking lot.</p>

<p><strong>From the East (Toronto Downtown Core) </strong></p>

<p>Take the Gardiner Expressway West to Hwy 427 North. Take the Dundas Street exit. You will come to a set of lights, Cloverdale Mall Rd. Travel straight ahead; this will lead you directly into the shopping centre parking lot.</p>

<p><strong>From the West</strong></p>

<p>Take the QEW East to Hwy 427 North. Exit at Cloverdale Mall Rd. Turn right on The East Mall. The shopping centre will be on your right side.<br />
<br>or<br /> <br />
Take Dundas Street East. Just under the Hwy 427 Bridge you will come to a set of lights, Cloverdale Mall Rd. Turn left, this will lead you directly into the shopping centre.<br />
<br>or<br /> <br />
Take Bloor Street East to The East Mall. Turn right on The East Mall, heading south. The Mall will be on your right hand side.</p>

<h2>Travelling by Transit</h2>

<p><strong>By TTC </strong></p>

<p>From the Kipling Subway Station take Route #111 East Mall. Depart the bus at The East Mall and Yarn Road. Cloverdale Mall is approximately a two minute walk from the bus stop.<br />
For more details on the Toronto Transit System please visit&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ttc.ca" target="_blank">www.ttc.ca</a>.</p>

<p><br />
<strong>By Mississauga Transit </strong></p>

<p>Take or connect to Route 1C Dundas East. Depart the bus at Billingham Road (Stop 9001), walk to the intersection of Dundas Street and The East Mall Crescent. Cloverdale Mall is approximately a five minute walk from bus stop.</p> <p>or</p><p>Take or connect to Route 3E Bloor East. Depart the bus at Bloor Street and The East Mall (stop 9027). Cloverdale Mall is approximately a two minute walk from the bus stop.<br />
For more details on the City of Mississauga Transit system please visit <a href="http://www.mississauga.ca/portal/residents/publictransit" target="_blank">www.mississauga.ca/portal/residents/publictransit</a>.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.cloverdalemall.com/pages/cloverdale-construction-in-the-area">Temporary Road Closures Near Cloverdale Mall</a></p>
